nd that this object was transported from the main belt into\nthe current comet-like orbit via the 3:1 mean motion resonance with Jupiter.\n  Conclusions. We conclude that the origins of ACOs can be more reliably\nidentified by adding polarimetric data to the color and spectral information.\nThis study would be valuable for investigating how the ice-bearing small bodies\ndistribute in the inner Solar System.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 30 Oct 2021 02:47:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
